  "rationale": "nyx-agent-scan.service runs `/usr/local/bin/nyx-agent scan --headless` from the timer at packaging/nyx-agent.timer:9 (Mon 03:00 every week, plus Persistent=true catch-up). The unit sets NoNewPrivileges + ProtectSystem=strict + ProtectHome=true + PrivateTmp=true, but it does NOT set `User=`, `DynamicUser=`, `Group=`, or any CapabilityBoundingSet. systemd's default for a Type=oneshot service with no User= is User=root, so the weekly scan runs as root with the full root ambient capability set (the bounding set is unrestricted by default; NoNewPrivileges only blocks setuid escalation, it does not drop caps already held). That is a regression against the sibling unit nyx-agent.service (packaging/nyx-agent.service:21), which correctly sets DynamicUser=yes + StateDirectory=nyx-agent + empty AmbientCapabilities/CapabilityBoundingSet — that one is hardened, this one is not. Why the divergence matters: every prior OS_COMMAND / PATH_TRAVERSAL / SSRF finding in this sentinel that fires on the *scan* code path (git ls-remote ext:: at router.rs:799, --since-ref option-injection at main.rs:1214, etc.) inherits the running uid. Under nyx-agent.service those primitives land in a DynamicUser-confined uid with strict / private filesystems; under nyx-agent-scan.service the same primitive lands as root with unrestricted caps. Worse, the two units do not share state: nyx-agent.service writes state under `%S/nyx-agent` (`/var/lib/nyx-agent` per StateDirectory) owned by the dynamic uid, while nyx-agent-scan.service has no StateDirectory and no NYX_AGENT_STATE_DIR env — so the timer-driven scan runs with whatever default the binary computes (typically `~root/.local/share/nyx` under Type=oneshot+User=root). The two state dirs diverge, the timer-driven scan's findings never land in the daemon's sqlite, and the operator-visible scan history skips every cron-fired run. Pass-7 explicitly said 'the systemd path is correctly hardened' — that claim only applied to nyx-agent.service. Concrete fix: add `User=nyx-agent` + `Group=nyx-agent` (created in postinst) OR `DynamicUser=yes` + `StateDirectory=nyx-agent`, plus `Environment=NYX_AGENT_STATE_DIR=%S/nyx-agent` to align with the daemon's state, plus `AmbientCapabilities=` + `CapabilityBoundingSet=` (empty) to match the sibling unit. Static pass missed because the hardening lives in YAML-like systemd unit syntax, not in any Rust crate, and the regression is the *absence* of directives, not a positive misconfiguration.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "n/a — defence is unit-file edits. Reproduce the privilege gap: `sudo systemctl start nyx-agent-scan.service && ps -o pid,user,cmd -C nyx-agent | grep scan` — the scan process runs as `root`. Then reproduce the state-divergence: `sudo find /var/lib/nyx-agent /root/.local/share/nyx -newer /etc/systemd/system/nyx-agent-scan.service 2>/dev/null` — fresh files only land under the second path, never the daemon's StateDirectory."
}

