  "suggested_payload_hint": "On a stock macOS install where the operator followed docs/triggers/cron.md verbatim: `cat /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.nyx.agent.plist | plutil -extract EnvironmentVariables.NYX_WEBHOOK_SECRET raw -` recovers the secret as any local user. Then `BODY='{\"ref\":\"refs/heads/main\"}'; SIG=\"sha256=$(printf '%s' \"$BODY\" | openssl dgst -sha256 -hmac \"$SECRET\" -hex | awk '{print $2}')\"; curl ...` succeeds against 127.0.0.1:8765/webhook/git. Fix: amend docs/triggers/webhook.md to (a) recommend a 0600 sidecar file sourced by a wrapper script, OR (b) point operators at a future `[triggers].webhook_secret_keychain` field that pulls from the macOS keychain via the existing `secrets` crate; never paste shared secrets into a LaunchDaemon plist."
