econd `sqlx::query(...).execute(&mut *tx)` as a write that returns Result and trusts the `await?` to surface failures, blind to the SQL semantics of zero-row UPDATEs, and (b) the test partner asserts the broken behaviour as intent, so a tests-first walker concludes the code is correct. Severity: data-integrity / provenance-tracking corruption — not RCE on its own, but it defeats the audit trail rows 1-14 assume is present when triaging AI-sourced findings, so any incident response that filters on `findings.attack_provenance IS NOT NULL` will miss the very rows the helper was meant to mark.",
