ape` plus any source file that triggers a rule whose flow steps reference `escape` walks the read_to_string through the symlink and the private key body lands in the LLM prompt. Distinct from pass-13 (which covers diag.rs:150 read_excerpt → evidence.source_excerpt → verdict_blob column → repro-bundle.tar): same primitive shape, different reader and different exfil channel — the pass-13 fix (allowlist subset before verdict_blob write OR strip before bundle render) does NOT close this hole, because the SpecDerivation pre-fetch reads the source bytes *fresh* off disk via Path::join, never touching evidence.source_excerpt or verdict_blob. Also distinct from pass-17 row 23 (workspace.rs symlink contract): that row notes the snapshot copies symlinks verbatim and the *contract* is unverified; this row is one of the concrete consumers that breaks the contract — even with the pass-17-recommended canonicalise-and-fence fix in workspace.rs, the absolute-path footgun on `Path::join` here still bites for any diag whose path is absolute. Also distinct from pass-17 prompt-injection on exploration.rs:338 (LLM-output trust): that row covers attacker text steering the model; this row covers attacker bytes landing inside the request payload that the model never sees as instructions — the LLM provider's *operator-visible request log* / *training corpus* / *attacker-controlled inference endpoint* is the disclosure surface. Static pass missed because (i) the sink is `fs::read_to_string` on a `PathBuf` built from Path::join — perfectly type-correct, and the function looks like a code-review helper, (ii) the writer (diag.path comes from nyx, looks operator-trusted) and the reader (LLM prompt body) cross two crate boundaries and an async task pipeline, (iii) the SpecDerivation outcome stores no per-call indicator of which excerpts were sent to the provider, so an operator auditing the agent.sqlite store sees only the synthesised harness spec, not the bytes that travelled with the prompt. Fix: in read_excerpt, after `let resolved = workspace_root.join(path)`, compute `let canon = resolved.canonicalize().ok()?; let root_canon = workspace_root.canonicalize().ok()?; if !canon.starts_with(&root_canon) { return None; }` — refuses absolute paths, `..` traversal, and symlinks that resolve outside the root in a single check; mirror the same fix in diag.rs:150 (the pass-13 reader) so both AI surface and bundle surface share one boundary helper.",
