- the only current caller (lane.rs:51-52) sets a wall-clock timeout, so today the OOM is bounded by the lane's deadline-to-OOM race. Future callers using `ScanOptions::default()` get `timeout: None` and the runaway is unbounded — flagged in the rationale's fix option (3) as the structural close (make `timeout: Duration` with a non-zero default, eliminate the Option arm).
- the resolve_binary PATH-lookup half is severable from the unbounded-read half — either fix lands a meaningful reduction in blast radius. Recommend landing fix options 1 + 3 first (capping + default-timeout) since they close the DoS lane; binary-attestation (option 4) is the right long-term close for the persistence/RCE half but requires operator-visible config (allowlist root + optional checksum pin).
- prior-pass rows 1-23 all STAND or remain in their prior STANDS-FIXED / STANDS-LATENT / STANDS-PARTIAL-FIX classifications; HEAD~3..HEAD adds ONE new file with ONE new row (pass-24) and otherwise carries only docstring cleanup, sandbox killed_by_operator instrumentation (pass-23 notes — security-neutral), ai_pipeline verifier trace persistence (audit-positive — see pass-23 notes carry-forward), and the markdown_code partial fix already classified in pass-23.
