    Adjacent multi-line `//` block at candidate_id() rewritten to
    drop the "Tracked under the candidate id-collision deferred
    item" sentence; pure comment edit.

threat-model walk (id-randomness change):
  * RNG choice: `rand::thread_rng()` in current `rand` crate is
    ChaCha12-seeded from the OS entropy pool — a CSPRNG. Suitable
    for any per-insert disambiguator; would also be suitable for
    a security token, though the suffix is only 32 bits (see
    next bullet).
  * Entropy: 32 bits = ~2^-32 collision probability per pair
    inside the same deterministic shard (finding_id × finished_at
    for PayloadRecord/HarnessSpecRecord; run_id × rank × created_at
    for ChainRecord; stable-hash × created_at × rank for
    candidate_id). Birthday-bound 50%-collision threshold inside
    one shard is ~77k inserts — comfortably above the per-shard
    cardinality the system generates (each shard is one millisecond
    of replay activity for a single finding/run). Acceptable for
    the documented purpose ("disambiguator"), NOT acceptable for
    capability-token use.
  * Determinism regression: the four id formatters were previously
    deterministic given the prompt response, ms-clock, and rank.
    They are now non-deterministic by design. Any consumer that
    relied on idempotent re-insert (UPSERT by id) for replay would
    now produce duplicate rows. Walked Store impl call-sites in
    crates/nyx-agent-core/src/store/ (grep for PayloadRecord /
    HarnessSpecRecord / ChainRecord write paths) — every insert
    site treats the id as an opaque PK with no UPSERT semantic,
    and the candidate id is keyed by `INSERT OR IGNORE` only at
    the candidate-dedupe call (which uses the *stable* prefix
    hash, not the full id, for the dedupe decision). So the
    determinism flip is contained.
  * Exposure surface: chain_id is the only one of the four
    surfaced through the router (optional ?chain_id= filter at
    router.rs:1163,1180; candidate.id is echoed at router.rs:1490
    inside an authn-gated response). No `GET /<kind>/<id>` path
    exists, so the 32-bit random suffix does not protect against
    or weaken any ID-guess primitive — the deterministic prefix
    already constrains the search space below what the bearer
    gate filters out. No new CRED_EXPOSURE / IDOR shape.
  * No new HTTP route, no new shell/sql/url builder, no new
    serialization sink. The format!() macros consume the
    short_token() output only as record-PK bytes.

re-validation summary (rows 1-27 against current HEAD + working
tree):
  - rows 1-27 all STAND. The diff touches no auth surface, no
    handler body, no fs/shell path, no sandbox plumbing, no
    setup.rs window, no events_ws upgrade hook. The four id
    formatter sites are downstream of all sensitive boundaries.
  - pass-27 PR_SET_PDEATHSIG carry-forwards STAND unchanged
    (sandbox shim untouched this session).

