{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent/src/ai_pipeline.rs",
  "line": 1719,
  "cap": "VERIFIER_FORENSIC_GAP",
  "endpoint": "<trace-store:agent_traces.verifier_blob — post-0003 schema>",
  "rationale": "build_verifier_blob persists only {spec_id, vuln_payload_sha256, vuln_exit_code, benign_payload_sha256, benign_exit_code}. It drops the four fields that actually determine a VerifyVerdict: VerifyRun.oracle_fired, VerifyRun.timed_out, VerifyResult.replay_stable, VerifyResult.error_message. Concretely: a Confirmed verdict (oracle_fired=true, exit_code=0) is indistinguishable in the blob from a Refuted verdict (oracle_fired=false, exit_code=0); a flaky Confirmed-then-Refuted pair caught by ChainRunner's replay_stable_check is indistinguishable from a clean Confirmed (replay_stable not recorded); a runner crash mid-spawn writes NULL verifier_blob via the early-error branch (drive_verify_for_candidate :1806 passes Some(spec_id?? no — None, None)) — but the migration comment says NULL means 'pre-migration row, fall back to verdict_blob join'. Post-0003 the trace viewer cannot distinguish 'pre-migration legacy' from 'post-migration verifier crashed before producing a result'. Two operationally critical states collapse to one NULL marker, defeating the audit purpose of the column. Static pass missed because each individual field write is correct; the gap is what is *not* in the schema.",
