record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent-api/src/webhook.rs",
  "line": 393,
  "cap": "AUTH_BYPASS",
  "endpoint": "POST /webhook/git (replay protection bypass via delivery-id forgery)",
  "rationale": "The new DeliveryDedupCache only keys on the upstream-provided X-GitHub-Delivery / X-Gitea-Delivery / etc. header. HMAC-SHA256 is computed over the request body only — no header is bound into the signature (verify_signature at :481-488), and the body itself carries no nonce or timestamp. Therefore an attacker who captures any one valid (body, signature) pair (TLS-MITM, proxy log, GHA-step echo, etc.) can replay the captured push event indefinitely by simply rotating X-GitHub-Delivery to a fresh UUID on each replay; the new dedup gate at :393 admits each replay as a fresh delivery. The branch filter at :447 is also satisfied because the body's `ref` is whatever the original push carried. Each replay re-fires ScanTrigger::trigger, costing repo clone + sandbox spin every time. Static pass missed because the replay primitive is the *header-not-bound-to-HMAC* gap; nothing about the dedup or HMAC code is individually wrong.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "Capture one legitimate POST /webhook/git (body B, sig S). Then loop: curl -X POST /webhook/git -H 'X-Hub-Signature-256: <S>' -H 'X-GitHub-Event: push' -H \"X-GitHub-Delivery: $(uuidgen)\" --data-binary @B — observe a fresh run_id per call."
}

