record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent/src/cmd/pr_comment.rs",
  "line": 371,
  "cap": "SSRF",
  "endpoint": "pr_comment GitHub-API client (operator-set GH_API_URL or PR override)",
  "rationale": "validate_gh_api_url enforces the IMDS / 169.254/16 / fe80::/10 deny-list by string-comparing the URL authority. Hosts are never parsed through std::net::IpAddr or url::Host, so non-canonical literals for the same address slip through: decimal `2130706433`, hex `0x7f000001`, octal `0177.000.000.001`, dotted-decimal `169.254.43518` (last-two-octets fused), and IPv4-mapped IPv6 `[::ffff:169.254.169.254]` all resolve to denied IPs at connect time but pass the prefix gate at :371. Combined with build_client (:395) shipping `Authorization: Bearer <PAT>` as a default header, an operator-controlled gh_api_url override forwards the GitHub PAT to whatever the OS resolves the bogus literal to — including AWS IMDSv1 at 169.254.169.254. Static pass missed because the sink (reqwest::Client::send) is correctly gated; the gap is the parser, not a tainted-flow edge.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "set GH_API_URL=http://2852039166/ (decimal for 169.254.169.254) or http://0xa9fea9fe/ ; on EC2, response body contains IAM role creds, which then post back to the attacker via the agent's normal PR-comment write loop."
}

