record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyctos-api/src/webhook.rs",
  "line": 385,
  "cap": "TRIGGER_CONFUSION",
  "endpoint": "POST /webhook/git (webhook_provider='sourcehut')",
  "rationale": "SourcehutExtractor parses the ref via `.strip_prefix(\"refs/heads/\").or(Some(r))` — the fallback was added to tolerate sr.ht builds that emit bare branch names, but it also accepts *non-branch* refs verbatim. A push of `refs/tags/v1.2.3` returns `branch=Some(\"refs/tags/v1.2.3\")`, which then flows into the webhook_branch allow-list comparator: if the operator sets `webhook_branch=\"refs/tags/v1.2.3\"` (or, more dangerously, leaves it `None` so all branches match), a tag push triggers a branch-shaped run. Downstream cloners that derive a working tree from this string will resolve `refs/heads/refs/tags/v1.2.3` and fail, but the run row, the dedup slot, and the audit row are already spent — a low-bandwidth DoS on the trigger pipeline. Symmetric to the Bitbucket finding: the producer-side ref-shape ambiguity becomes a trigger-side correctness failure. Static pass missed because both `strip_prefix` and `or(Some)` are individually safe.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "POST a sr.ht webhook body `{\"event\":{\"refs\":[{\"name\":\"refs/tags/v1.2.3\"}]}}` with webhook_branch unset; verify a triggered run with branch field literally `refs/tags/v1.2.3` and observe the downstream clone failure burning the dedup slot."
}

