record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent/src/ai_pipeline.rs",
  "line": 141,
  "cap": "BUDGET_BYPASS",
  "rationale": "BudgetStoreTracker::add_spend is unconditional: it inserts the row (ensure_default) then issues a bare `UPDATE budgets SET spent = spent + ? RETURNING …`, never comparing the new total against cap_usd_micros. The cap check lives upstream in the adapter as a separate `tracker.cap()` + `tracker.current_spend()` pre-roundtrip read; add_spend only fires *after* the (already-paid-for) AI call returns. Combined with the `max_concurrent_one_shot` Semaphore at run_payload_synthesis_pass:197 (default ≥1, AiConfig::max_concurrent_one_shot_resolved typically 4), N concurrent fan-out tasks each pass the same gate snapshot, dispatch, and only then settle their spend — total spend can land at cap + (N-1)*per_call without any code path refusing or refunding. The regression test at ai_pipeline.rs:2670 asserts `spent_usd_micros == 8_000` for 8×1000-micro concurrent add_spends *without* ever asserting the cap was respected, baking the bypass into the test surface. Static pass missed because the bug is a check-then-act TOCTOU spanning two SQL roundtrips + an N-task fan-out — no single function shows a tainted-flow sink to a cap-relaxed write. Fix shape: collapse to a single atomic `UPDATE budgets SET spent = spent + ? WHERE spent + ? <= cap RETURNING spent, cap`, surface the WHERE-fail as `BudgetExceeded`, and have the adapter reserve spend *before* the AI roundtrip with a refund on actual cost delta.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "test: cap=1_000_000, max_concurrent_one_shot=4, queue 8 PayloadSynthesis inputs whose simulated per-call cost is 400_000; observe row.spent_usd_micros > cap_usd_micros after the join and zero BudgetExceeded errors on the wire."
}

